                        </header><!-- .entry-header -->

                        <div class="entry-content mt-5">
                            <p>The founder of Yengat Birhan Charity Organization, s/r Meseret Tesfaye started its work as a volunteer by the financial support of her family. First she engaged in a small scale support of disadvantageous families in Yeka Sub city, Woreda 08 in 2014. The founder says that, 2006 made her to think critically about life unlike other times. It was during the delivery of her third child that she was on the brink of death. That dangerous event showed her that life was too short on earth, and not as long as she expected. It also encouraged her to ask herself, “What am I supposed to do with these newly given additional years?” “What must I do in order to live a meaningful life and to have life satisfaction?” Then she found that helping people to live a better life will be the number one yearning in her heart, deep inside. She started the work by strengthening the least privileged families especially the single mom who suffers/ struggling to support their children. At that time the support includes: helping the single Mom’s to engage in income generating activities and provide school materials including school uniform for school children once in a year and counseling on health issues.</p>
