                                    <div class="cause-content-wrap">
                                        <header class="entry-header d-flex flex-wrap align-items-center">
                                            <h3 class="entry-title w-100 m-0"><a href="#">Economic Empowerment</a></h3>
                                        </header><!-- .entry-header -->

                                        <div class="entry-content">
                                            <p class="m-0">To improve the economic status on the family level: From 70 families, we select one woman from each family and put them in self-help groups (15 to 20). Weekly meetings to discuss common issues on business and other social issues, Education on how to improve their savings to enable them engage in income generating activities, Encourage them contribute to a group savings according to their financial strength. This to help resolve problems that may arise in the course of their business, Organizing basic business skills training to familiarize them to the business world Asset them to develop their own business plan, Facilitate finance to them to start their business and Weekly follow ups on their progress in their respective ventures.</p>
                                        </div><!-- .entry-content -->

                                       
                                    </div><!-- .cause-content-wrap -->
                                </div><!-- .cause-wrap -->
                            </div><!-- .swiper-slide -->

                            <div class="swiper-slide">
                                <div class="cause-wrap">
                                    

                                    <div class="cause-content-wrap">
                                        <header class="entry-header d-flex flex-wrap align-items-center">
                                            <h3 class="entry-title w-100 m-0"><a href="#">Educational Empowerment</a></h3>
                                        </header><!-- .entry-header -->

                                        <div class="entry-content">
                                            <p class="m-0">Currently we facilitate access to education for 80 orphan children of Yeka sub-city Wereda 08, who is vulnerable to school drop-out through providing education material support and tutorial class and assist to successfully completed their education. Girl child will get priority. Providing educational materials including school uniforms and school bags once per year, Organizing tutorials classes on basic subjects, like English and mathematics, Providing a cup of milk and bread for each student as a supper before the tutorials class, Follow up programs, in their home and in their school, at the end of each semester to ensure regular school attendance and satisfactory academic performance and Psycho social activity like playing game or visiting some recreational place and awarding for the top student.</p>
                                        </div><!-- .entry-content -->

                                        
                                    </div><!-- .cause-content-wrap -->
                                </div><!-- .cause-wrap -->
                            </div><!-- .swiper-slide -->

                            <div class="swiper-slide">
                                <div class="cause-wrap">
                                    

                                    <div class="cause-content-wrap">
                                        <header class="entry-header d-flex flex-wrap align-items-center">
                                            <h3 class="entry-title w-100 m-0"><a href="#">Health Empowerment</a></h3>
                                        </header><!-- .entry-header -->

                                        <div class="entry-content">
                                            <p class="m-0">By improving the health seeking behavior of the mother, to prevent new HIV infection, Psychological support for people living with HIV and nutrition care/services of single mothers and orphan children through providing health education and information.For the women, Health education to improve their knowledge on basic health and nutrition care/service on monthly basis for self-help groups&how to prevent new HIV infection and Psychological support for people living with HIV, Home visits supervise and advise on health related issues and possibly linking them to government health centers. For Children, Select one elementary and a high school to give health education; such as on personal hygiene, reproductive health, including HIV/AIDS and drug addiction.</p>
                                        </div><!-- .entry-content -->

                                        
                                    </div><!-- .cause-content-wrap -->
